race.comment: EXTRA HANDS (10) has been disappointing at her last couple, most recently over 1200m at Wagga which was too short. Raced once over this distance and filled a minor placing here. Best figures read well so give her another chance, particularly with the winkers going on. SENSESATIONAL STAR (11) has found the line okay and finished on the placegetters' heels at both runs this time in work over sharper trips. Nicely in with the claim and looking for this sort of journey at the third run back. GINNO'S HALO (2) came with a big finish but just failed to pick up the winner last time out over 1400m at Wagga. Fitter for two runs back from a spell and this slightly longer trip is to his advantage. DEFLECTOR (9) registered her seventh minor placing from 11 starts when edged out over 1600m here last start. Only needs to hold that form to be right in contention. The lightly raced TALISTIANA (12) is fitter for two runs back from a spell and can play a role in the outcome.
